  "prompt": "Does Reliance JIO 4G require internet to make voice calls?",
  "response": "Reliance Jio's 4G network utilizes **VoLTE (Voice over LTE)** technology to handle voice calls. Here's what that means for users:\n\n1. **Integrated Voice and Data:** \n   - **VoLTE** allows voice calls to be transmitted over the same 4G LTE data network that you use for internet browsing, streaming, and other data services.\n   \n2. **No Separate Internet Required for Calls:**\n   - While voice calls technically use data protocols, you **do not need a separate or active internet connection** (like Wi-Fi or mobile data in addition to your main plan) to make and receive voice calls on Jio 4G.\n   - Your standard Jio 4G service plan covers both voice and data functionalities seamlessly.\n\n3. **Benefits of VoLTE on Jio:**\n   - **Higher Call Quality:** VoLTE typically offers clearer and more reliable call quality compared to traditional voice calls.\n   - **Simultaneous Voice and Data:** You can use voice and data services simultaneously without interrupting each other. For example, you can be on a call and browse the internet at the same time.\n   - **Faster Call Setup:** Calls connect faster compared to older network technologies.\n\n4. **Requirements:**\n   - **Compatible Device:** Ensure your smartphone supports VoLTE and is compatible with Jio's network.\n   - **Active 4G Plan:** You need to be on a Jio 4G plan that includes VoLTE services.\n\n**In Summary:**\nWhile Reliance Jio 4G voice calls operate over the LTE data network using VoLTE technology, you **do not need a separate internet connection** to make voice calls. The voice and data services are integrated into your standard Jio 4G plan, providing seamless connectivity for both calling and internet usage.",
